890
00:54:04,165 --> 00:54:06,209
- What is this?

891
00:54:06,210 --> 00:54:07,359
Where am I?

892
00:54:07,360 --> 00:54:09,609
- You're on God's good earth.

893
00:54:09,610 --> 00:54:10,883
Fresno, California.

894
00:54:13,560 --> 00:54:15,643
- Did I have a heart attack?

895
00:54:15,644 --> 00:54:17,024
- No.

896
00:54:17,025 --> 00:54:19,755
Just shorted out from exhaustion.

897
00:54:19,756 --> 00:54:21,721
Wife's a nurse.

898
00:54:21,722 --> 00:54:22,722
- Oh.

899
00:54:25,554 --> 00:54:27,971
What kind of a place is this?

900
00:54:28,833 --> 00:54:29,833
- Look up there.

901
00:54:31,050 --> 00:54:32,050
See anything?

902
00:54:35,180 --> 00:54:36,863
- A ceiling painted with clouds.

903
00:54:38,292 --> 00:54:39,292
- That all?

904
00:54:40,420 --> 00:54:41,420
Scoot over.

905
00:54:43,830 --> 00:54:45,763
Don't worry. I'm a minister.

906
00:54:50,720 --> 00:54:53,303
Eddie Corbett at your service.

907
00:54:58,360 --> 00:55:00,083
Go on. Give it a try.

908
00:55:04,540 --> 00:55:06,666
- Frosty the Snowman, I don't know.

909
00:55:06,667 --> 00:55:08,664
(Eddie chuckles)

910
00:55:08,665 --> 00:55:09,665
- You see the chin?

911
00:55:13,370 --> 00:55:14,420
The line in the nose.

912
00:55:16,130 --> 00:55:17,130
The eyes.

913
00:55:18,710 --> 00:55:20,339
Right there.

914
00:55:20,340 --> 00:55:21,340
Pure Odalis.

915
00:55:24,132 --> 00:55:27,993
Just goes to show things
aren't always what they seem.

916
00:55:31,615 --> 00:55:32,615
Here you go.

917
00:55:34,540 --> 00:55:35,540
Eat up.

918
00:55:36,540 --> 00:55:38,777
We'll have you back on
your feet in no time.

919
00:55:41,330 --> 00:55:42,497
- How did I...

920
00:55:48,140 --> 00:55:51,390
(soft, midtempo music)

921
00:55:58,623 --> 00:55:59,790
- Kinda bored.

922
00:56:01,775 --> 00:56:05,025
(soft, midtempo music)

923
00:56:51,417 --> 00:56:52,364
(sizzling)

924
00:56:52,365 --> 00:56:53,515
- Ow!

925
00:56:53,516 --> 00:56:54,834
Freak!

926
00:56:54,835 --> 00:56:55,918
- [Cam] Ouch.

927
00:56:57,020 --> 00:56:59,129
- [Eddie] You forget how
to tie your shoes, kid?

928
00:56:59,130 --> 00:57:02,249
- No, no, no, no, hey,
hey, whoa, I'm fine.

929
00:57:02,250 --> 00:57:03,649
Hallelujah.

930
00:57:03,650 --> 00:57:06,209
- So let's talk about Mr. Fish.

931
00:57:06,210 --> 00:57:07,960
Who wants to tell me what happened?

932
00:57:10,560 --> 00:57:11,560
Cameron?

933
00:57:13,620 --> 00:57:15,479
Come on, big man.

934
00:57:15,480 --> 00:57:18,479
Tell me what it's like to be
taken away from your life,

935
00:57:18,480 --> 00:57:20,740
your home, your loved ones.

936
00:57:24,830 --> 00:57:25,830
- We messed up.

937
00:57:26,580 --> 00:57:27,580
- That's right.

938
00:57:28,260 --> 00:57:29,260
You messed up.

939
00:57:31,550 --> 00:57:33,600
What do you have to add to that, Crystal?

940
00:57:37,200 --> 00:57:38,503
- He was asking for it.

941
00:57:42,630 --> 00:57:43,510
- If you hurt somebody else,

942
00:57:43,511 --> 00:57:45,810
does that make you feel
better about yourself?

943
00:57:48,430 --> 00:57:49,430
Look at me.

944
00:57:52,540 --> 00:57:53,540
You can stop this.

945
00:57:56,400 --> 00:58:00,563
You can change this
self-destructive path you're on.

946
00:58:01,870 --> 00:58:05,163
You don't think you have it
in you, but I know you do.

947
00:58:09,430 --> 00:58:10,783
So what about you, Jodi?

948
00:58:18,876 --> 00:58:20,576
You know you did wrong, don't you?

949
00:58:29,301 --> 00:58:30,951
There you go.

950
00:58:30,952 --> 00:58:31,866
(sizzling)
Ow!

951
00:58:31,867 --> 00:58:36,866
(Eddie grunts)
(Cam laughing)

952
00:58:38,738 --> 00:58:43,581
Now just remember, what
goes around comes around.

953
00:58:43,582 --> 00:58:44,415
- [Employee] Res-Wel Motel.

954
00:58:44,416 --> 00:58:46,342
Yeah, a guy here claims
he being kidnapped.

955
00:58:46,343 --> 00:58:47,779
- [Gordon] I am being kidnapped.

956
00:58:47,780 --> 00:58:48,873
- [Employee] Now hurry.

957
00:58:48,874 --> 00:58:49,707
(banging)

958
00:58:49,708 --> 00:58:51,148
- [Gordon] Now why did you say that?

959
00:58:57,520 --> 00:58:59,179
- Well, that's it.

960
00:58:59,180 --> 00:59:00,543
- I don't understand.

961
00:59:01,380 --> 00:59:02,380
What was that?

962
00:59:02,381 --> 00:59:04,469
- I take it those weren't
his grandchildren?

963
00:59:04,470 --> 00:59:05,330
- Of course not.

964
00:59:05,331 --> 00:59:07,673
Clearly he was in fear for his life.

965
00:59:11,450 --> 00:59:13,199
- This is a registration for a hand gun

966
00:59:13,200 --> 00:59:15,819
purchased December 2nd by your father.

967
00:59:15,820 --> 00:59:18,009
Same gun you saw him
holding on those girls.

968
00:59:18,010 --> 00:59:19,889
- So just what exactly
are you trying to say?

969
00:59:19,890 --> 00:59:21,489
- He probably was kidnapped.

970
00:59:21,490 --> 00:59:23,019
- Probably? What else could it be?

971
00:59:23,020 --> 00:59:25,049
- Well, there is some confusion.

972
00:59:25,050 --> 00:59:27,239
Your father was stopped in Southern Oregon

973
00:59:27,240 --> 00:59:30,282
and there were three very
nervous minors in the car.

974
00:59:30,283 --> 00:59:32,429
- Oh my god.

975
00:59:32,430 --> 00:59:34,789
- Now we're running a
check on them right now.

976
00:59:34,790 --> 00:59:37,809
In the meantime, we're
not ruling anything out.

977
00:59:37,810 --> 00:59:40,329
Well I guess we can rule out suicide.

978
00:59:40,330 --> 00:59:41,873
Anyway, I'll be in touch.

979
00:59:44,850 --> 00:59:46,289
You know, I wasn't gonna
to say anything about this,

980
00:59:46,290 --> 00:59:50,600
but the guy who shot this
said that he wants $5,000

981
00:59:50,601 --> 00:59:52,633
or he's going to sell
it to Primetime Crime.

982
00:59:53,620 --> 00:59:56,169
- What?
- I think it's just a bluff.

983
00:59:56,170 --> 00:59:58,670
I mean, what would Primetime
Crime want with this?

984
00:59:59,570 --> 01:00:02,820
(soft, midtempo music)

985
01:00:03,822 --> 01:00:06,579
♪ Hope and prayin' ♪

986
01:00:06,580 --> 01:00:09,356
♪ I've been waitin' ♪

987
01:00:09,357 --> 01:00:13,607
♪ Everybody needs somebody to love ♪

988
01:00:20,640 --> 01:00:23,354
♪ There's no question ♪

989
01:00:23,355 --> 01:00:26,436
♪ Straight from heaven ♪

990
01:00:26,437 --> 01:00:28,903
♪ You're my angel ♪

991
01:00:28,904 --> 01:00:30,206
- Hello?

992
01:00:30,207 --> 01:00:31,763
Hello? Anybody around?

993
01:00:33,390 --> 01:00:34,390
Mr. Corbett?

994
01:00:35,960 --> 01:00:37,663
- You can call me Eddie, Mr. Fish.

995
01:00:39,964 --> 01:00:41,364
- You can call me Mr. Trout.

996
01:00:43,570 --> 01:00:44,593
- Hey, I was close.

997
01:00:45,637 --> 01:00:46,937
You want to go for a walk?

998
01:00:47,790 --> 01:00:48,623
It might do you some good.

999
01:00:48,624 --> 01:00:50,339
- Well I was trying to use the telephone

1000
01:00:50,340 --> 01:00:52,640
but I couldn't find one
anywhere in the house.

1001
01:00:53,520 --> 01:00:56,669
I must've left my cell phone
up where I was chopping wood.

1002
01:00:56,670 --> 01:00:58,003
Come on. I'll take you to it.

1003
01:01:02,000 --> 01:01:04,879
I spent most of my youth
getting in and out of trouble.

1004
01:01:04,880 --> 01:01:07,923
Followed it up with 36
years of serious drifting.

1005
01:01:09,080 --> 01:01:11,323
And then bam, I was convicted by the Lord.

1006
01:01:12,610 --> 01:01:15,523
I've only been a full senior
pastor for about a year.

1007
01:01:17,110 --> 01:01:20,053
Proof that it's never too late to change.

1008
01:01:21,057 --> 01:01:22,259
- Where is this phone?

1009
01:01:22,260 --> 01:01:23,310
- We're almost there.

1010
01:01:25,050 --> 01:01:26,010
You holding up okay?

1011
01:01:26,011 --> 01:01:28,119
- Yeah, yeah. I just
have to call the police.

1012
01:01:28,120 --> 01:01:29,120
- There it is.

1013
01:01:32,100 --> 01:01:32,933
(Jodi and Crystal chuckle)

1014
01:01:32,934 --> 01:01:35,713
- There's something you
don't see these days.

1015
01:01:38,460 --> 01:01:41,019
Straight out of Norman Rockwell.

1016
01:01:41,020 --> 01:01:42,440
Just kids being kids.

1017
01:01:43,494 --> 01:01:45,744
(laughing)

1018
01:01:50,331 --> 01:01:52,432
- [Cam] Push me higher!

1019
01:01:52,433 --> 01:01:55,080
(laughing)

1020
01:01:55,081 --> 01:01:56,499
- It's them.

1021
01:01:56,500 --> 01:01:58,379
They're the ones who kidnapped me.

1022
01:01:58,380 --> 01:02:00,029
Give me the phone. Quick.

1023
01:02:00,030 --> 01:02:01,830
- You mean Crystal and Cam and Jodi?

1024
01:02:02,926 --> 01:02:04,496
- You know them?

1025
01:02:04,497 --> 01:02:06,509
Do you have any idea what they did to me?

1026
01:02:06,510 --> 01:02:08,163
- Well yeah.

1027
01:02:08,164 --> 01:02:10,424
I think it's great you're
sticking with them.

1028
01:02:10,425 --> 01:02:11,258
- I'm not sticking with them.

1029
01:02:11,259 --> 01:02:12,410
Did they tell you that?

1030
01:02:15,760 --> 01:02:17,869
How do you work this cockamamie thing?

1031
01:02:17,870 --> 01:02:18,870
- Push send.

1032
01:02:22,956 --> 01:02:24,206
- [Cam] Higher!

1033
01:02:25,180 --> 01:02:26,164
- Gordon.

1034
01:02:26,165 --> 01:02:27,329
(Cam thuds)

1035
01:02:27,330 --> 01:02:30,343
If there's one thing these
kids need, it's consistency.

1036
01:02:31,280 --> 01:02:33,369
God knows they didn't get it at home.

1037
01:02:33,370 --> 01:02:35,229
- How would you know?

1038
01:02:35,230 --> 01:02:38,789
- I ran a halfway house
for runaways up in Seattle,

1039
01:02:38,790 --> 01:02:40,739
right after I got out of seminary.

1040
01:02:40,740 --> 01:02:43,183
- [Gordon] Well I can't
vouch for your work, Eddie.

1041
01:02:45,090 --> 01:02:47,990
- They could have left you up
on that mountain top to die.

1042
01:02:49,340 --> 01:02:50,889
That kid, Cam?

1043
01:02:50,890 --> 01:02:53,163
He gave you mouth-to-mouth resuscitation.

1044
01:02:54,690 --> 01:02:57,329
You didn't need it, but
he didn't know that.

1045
01:02:57,330 --> 01:02:58,819
- What's wrong with this thing?

1046
01:02:58,820 --> 01:03:00,323
I can't get through to 911.

1047
01:03:01,260 --> 01:03:03,310
- Call the operator. They'll connect you.

1048
01:03:07,499 --> 01:03:10,079
I don't know, maybe you're right.

1049
01:03:10,080 --> 01:03:12,030
Maybe they would be better off in jail.

1050
01:03:13,550 --> 01:03:17,313
Tried as adults, put in
with hardened criminals.

1051
01:03:20,320 --> 01:03:22,743
Can't be any worse than
what they grew up in.

1052
01:03:24,670 --> 01:03:26,139
Crystal learned the meaning of hot

1053
01:03:26,140 --> 01:03:28,290
when her mother burned
her with cigarettes.

1054
01:03:29,149 --> 01:03:30,345
- [Operator] Hello, this is the operator.

1055
01:03:30,346 --> 01:03:31,509
How may I help you?

1056
01:03:31,510 --> 01:03:32,789
- Hello. Uh, yes.

1057
01:03:32,790 --> 01:03:35,449
Could you please connect
me to the local police?

1058
01:03:35,450 --> 01:03:36,973
This is an emergency.
- Look.

1059
01:03:38,600 --> 01:03:42,349
Those kids did a terrible
thing kidnapping you,

1060
01:03:42,350 --> 01:03:45,259
but they're young and they can change.

1061
01:03:45,260 --> 01:03:46,860
They're at a critical point now.

1062
01:03:48,100 --> 01:03:49,593
So I'm asking you, Gordon.

1063
01:03:52,120 --> 01:03:53,713
I'll beg you if I have to.

1064
01:03:55,660 --> 01:03:58,069
I want just one adult besides myself

1065
01:03:58,070 --> 01:03:59,933
giving these kids another chance.

1066
01:04:03,250 --> 01:04:04,250
I'm finished.

1067
01:04:05,050 --> 01:04:06,800
- [Man] Fresno Police, please hold.

1068
01:04:07,835 --> 01:04:09,517
- [Eddie] It's up to you and God now.

1069
01:04:14,627 --> 01:04:16,923
- [Man] Fresno Police
Department, may I help you?

1070
01:04:18,010 --> 01:04:18,843
Hello?

1071
01:04:18,844 --> 01:04:20,379
- Hello.

1072
01:04:20,380 --> 01:04:21,500
Yes. I'd like to...

1073
01:04:27,940 --> 01:04:28,940
Nevermind.

1074
01:04:29,806 --> 01:04:32,166
(Eddie sighs)

1075
01:04:32,167 --> 01:04:33,823
How do you hang up this thing?

1076
01:04:36,286 --> 01:04:38,286
- God bless you, Gordon.

1077
01:04:40,400 --> 01:04:43,143
Where would any of us be
without a second chance?

1078
01:04:46,475 --> 01:04:49,286
- [Cam] Hey, Fish-Man, back from the dead!

1079
01:04:49,287 --> 01:04:51,501
- [Crystal] Fish-man,
Fish-man, he's our man.

1080
01:04:51,502 --> 01:04:53,991
If he can't do it, no one can!
- Gordon!

1081
01:04:53,992 --> 01:04:54,964
Where are you going?

1082
01:04:54,964 --> 01:04:55,964
- Listen.

1083
01:04:57,090 --> 01:04:59,709
I know you're anxious to get going,

1084
01:04:59,710 --> 01:05:01,409
but how'd you like to join me for a soak

1085
01:05:01,410 --> 01:05:03,189
in my healing waters?
- Thank you,

1086
01:05:03,190 --> 01:05:04,519
but I really must get home.

1087
01:05:04,520 --> 01:05:05,490
I must.

1088
01:05:05,491 --> 01:05:09,199
- [Eddie] Well your car's in
the driveway behind the garage.

1089
01:05:09,200 --> 01:05:10,250
It's been a pleasure.

1090
01:05:18,230 --> 01:05:19,230
- Hi.

1091
01:05:19,920 --> 01:05:21,548
I'm glad you're feeling better.

1092
01:05:21,549 --> 01:05:23,059
- Yes I am.

1093
01:05:23,060 --> 01:05:24,749
- I bought you this.

1094
01:05:24,750 --> 01:05:26,939
It's kind of a get well present.

1095
01:05:26,940 --> 01:05:27,990
- It's not necessary.

1096
01:05:34,040 --> 01:05:36,659
- Bottle of aspirin, extra strength,

1097
01:05:36,660 --> 01:05:38,473
Dr. Scholl's bunion pads,

1098
01:05:39,720 --> 01:05:44,219
tube of Colgate, and a toothbrush.

1099
01:05:44,220 --> 01:05:45,470
Medium bristle, not firm.

1100
01:05:48,540 --> 01:05:49,543
- No Bromo?

1101
01:05:55,090 --> 01:05:56,563
I am dying to brush my teeth.

1102
01:05:58,836 --> 01:06:01,086
(brushing)

1103
01:06:05,654 --> 01:06:06,654
Blegh.

1104
01:06:11,785 --> 01:06:15,059
- She's a good one.

1105
01:06:15,060 --> 01:06:16,329
- [Gordon] Well she's a lot
different than the other two,

1106
01:06:16,330 --> 01:06:17,609
I'll give you that.

1107
01:06:17,610 --> 01:06:19,500
- This reunion with her mother...

1108
01:06:22,068 --> 01:06:24,103
I pray that it's going to work out.

1109
01:06:25,680 --> 01:06:28,409
But I got to tell you,
I have serious doubts.

1110
01:06:28,410 --> 01:06:30,710
She's just not going to
make it on the street.

1111
01:06:31,830 --> 01:06:34,039
If it wasn't for Cam looking after her,

1112
01:06:34,040 --> 01:06:36,580
God knows what would've happened.

1113
01:06:39,420 --> 01:06:41,120
Something's bothering me, brother.

1114
01:06:43,860 --> 01:06:45,010
Why were you kidnapped?

1115
01:06:47,730 --> 01:06:48,730
- What?

1116
01:06:49,876 --> 01:06:51,629
- Have you thought about that?

1117
01:06:51,630 --> 01:06:53,663
I mean, in the deeper sense.

1118
01:06:55,652 --> 01:06:57,719
- What are you talking about?

1119
01:06:57,720 --> 01:06:59,619
- Bear with me here a moment,

1120
01:06:59,620 --> 01:07:02,120
'cause I've been giving
this some serious thought.

1121
01:07:04,620 --> 01:07:07,253
Now I don't know what's
been going on in your life,

1122
01:07:08,400 --> 01:07:10,679
but it's my belief that somehow,

1123
01:07:10,680 --> 01:07:12,583
some way God came through for you.

1124
01:07:14,913 --> 01:07:15,916
It's something to think about.

1125
01:07:15,917 --> 01:07:18,926
- You're some operator, you know that?

1126
01:07:18,927 --> 01:07:20,929
But you're wasting your time.

1127
01:07:20,930 --> 01:07:23,430
I'm not about to be baptized
here in your hot tub.

1128
01:07:24,552 --> 01:07:25,703
(Cam yells)

1129
01:07:25,704 --> 01:07:28,037
(splashing)

1130
01:07:36,337 --> 01:07:39,314
I think you better let him up.

1131
01:07:39,315 --> 01:07:41,448
(Cam gasps)
- Sorry, kid, I scare ya?

1132
01:07:41,449 --> 01:07:42,626
(Cam gasps)

1133
01:07:42,627 --> 01:07:44,989
(splashing)
Good.

1134
01:07:44,990 --> 01:07:46,382
Just a little private matter.

1135
01:07:46,383 --> 01:07:49,459
He reminds me of me at his age.

1136
01:07:49,460 --> 01:07:50,293
- I can see that.

1137
01:07:50,294 --> 01:07:52,133
I don't know which one of you is worse.

1138
01:07:53,580 --> 01:07:56,080
(Cam gasping)

1139
01:07:58,334 --> 01:08:01,049
(Cam laughs)

1140
01:08:01,050 --> 01:08:02,500
- It's a long haul, Fish-Man,

1141
01:08:03,594 --> 01:08:05,894
so I thought you could
use some driving music.

1142
01:08:07,799 --> 01:08:09,249
- What about my credit cards?

1143
01:08:17,100 --> 01:08:18,399
- [Jodi] Hey, wait, wait.

1144
01:08:18,400 --> 01:08:19,600
You didn't sign my cast.

1145
01:08:26,434 --> 01:08:27,267
(smacks)

1146
01:08:27,268 --> 01:08:29,419
(Crystal chuckles)
- Sorry.

1147
01:08:29,420 --> 01:08:31,493
I guess you weren't such a dud after all.

1148
01:08:36,410 --> 01:08:37,560
- Thanks again, Gordon.

1149
01:08:38,839 --> 01:08:40,349
You sure you don't want to trade?

1150
01:08:40,350 --> 01:08:44,539
This baby would make a terrific
prize for the church raffle.

1151
01:08:44,540 --> 01:08:45,540
- I don't think so.

1152
01:08:49,365 --> 01:08:51,782
(soft music)

1153
01:09:05,489 --> 01:09:08,739
(police siren wailing)

1154
01:09:17,620 --> 01:09:20,016
- [Officer 1] Three kids, right?

1155
01:09:20,017 --> 01:09:20,850
(police radio chatter)

1156
01:09:20,851 --> 01:09:22,583
I don't see 'em.

1157
01:09:22,584 --> 01:09:23,550
(police radio chatter)

1158
01:09:23,551 --> 01:09:26,309
- [Officer 2] They're probably
armed. Watch yourself.

1159
01:09:26,310 --> 01:09:27,573
Okay, check the floor.

1160
01:09:29,020 --> 01:09:30,238
- [Officer 1] They're not in here.

1161
01:09:30,239 --> 01:09:32,819
- All right, you can
put your hands down now.

1162
01:09:32,820 --> 01:09:34,539
You want to open the trunk, please?

1163
01:09:34,540 --> 01:09:36,489
- Can I ask you what you're looking for?

1164
01:09:36,490 --> 01:09:37,969
I'm on my way back to Seattle.

1165
01:09:37,970 --> 01:09:39,620
I've got a long trip ahead of me.

1166
01:09:44,120 --> 01:09:45,529
- All right. Where'd the kids go?

1167
01:09:45,530 --> 01:09:47,329
- Well they're not in there.

1168
01:09:47,330 --> 01:09:48,330
- Where are they?

1169
01:09:49,490 --> 01:09:51,290
- I've decided not to press charges.

1170
01:09:53,000 --> 01:09:56,019
- Let me explain something
to you. Mr. Trout.

1171
01:09:56,020 --> 01:09:58,249
Interstate kidnapping
is a serious offense.

1172
01:09:58,250 --> 01:09:59,539
Now just because you've decided

1173
01:09:59,540 --> 01:10:00,649
you don't want to press charges,

1174
01:10:00,650 --> 01:10:03,199
that doesn't mean a crime
hasn't been committed.

1175
01:10:03,200 --> 01:10:04,609
Now you're going to have
to come down to the station

1176
01:10:04,610 --> 01:10:05,829
and answer some questions.

1177
01:10:05,830 --> 01:10:07,190
- How long is this going to take?

1178
01:10:07,191 --> 01:10:10,071
- You want to ride with us or
do you want to follow behind?

1179
01:10:10,072 --> 01:10:13,072
(soft, tense music)

1180
01:10:24,907 --> 01:10:28,157
(police radio chatter)

1181
01:10:30,064 --> 01:10:33,064
(soft, tense music)

1182
01:10:46,281 --> 01:10:49,864
(train track bell ringing)

1183
01:10:51,824 --> 01:10:54,824
(train horn blares)

1184
01:11:05,767 --> 01:11:09,184
(soft, mysterious music)

1185
01:11:40,543 --> 01:11:42,474
- [Gordon] Changed my mind.

1186
01:11:42,475 --> 01:11:43,939
- You want to be baptized?

1187
01:11:43,940 --> 01:11:46,939
- I want to trade. My Cadi for your truck.

1188
01:11:46,940 --> 01:11:48,579
But it's got to run.

1189
01:11:48,580 --> 01:11:49,500
- [Eddie] It runs all right,

1190
01:11:49,501 --> 01:11:51,954
but it's still not an even trade.

1191
01:11:51,955 --> 01:11:55,038
(soft, upbeat music)

1192
01:12:02,720 --> 01:12:05,194
- [Gordon] Now, let's
say we get this started.

1193
01:12:05,195 --> 01:12:07,500
Get Jodi by Christmas.

1194
01:12:07,501 --> 01:12:08,834
- [Jodi] Thanks.

1195
01:12:10,022 --> 01:12:14,629
♪ All I know is there is a piece to find ♪

1196
01:12:14,630 --> 01:12:16,216
♪ Can I fight the fear ♪

1197
01:12:16,217 --> 01:12:21,217
♪ Can I find a way to fly, yeah ♪

1198
01:12:22,933 --> 01:12:26,277
♪ And be free to hope
just a little taller ♪

1199
01:12:26,278 --> 01:12:28,715
♪ Free to hope just a little more ♪

1200
01:12:28,716 --> 01:12:30,609
♪ Free to fly so much higher ♪

1201
01:12:30,610 --> 01:12:33,436
♪ Than I ever thought I could before ♪

1202
01:12:33,437 --> 01:12:35,652
♪ Free to laugh just a little longer ♪

1203
01:12:35,653 --> 01:12:38,059
♪ Free to love like you want me to, Lord ♪

1204
01:12:38,060 --> 01:12:40,888
♪ Take me to that place ♪

1205
01:12:40,889 --> 01:12:44,556
♪ Where I'm free to be free ♪

1206
01:12:56,274 --> 01:13:00,357
(bright, upbeat Christmas music)

1207
01:13:17,631 --> 01:13:20,471
- Your little brothers are
gonna flip over these guys.

1208
01:13:20,472 --> 01:13:22,519
(Gordon laughs)

1209
01:13:22,520 --> 01:13:24,729
- Can you give me the paper
with the shiny gold trim?

1210
01:13:24,730 --> 01:13:25,563
They're for my mom.

1211
01:13:25,563 --> 01:13:26,396
- [Employee] Certainly.

1212
01:13:26,397 --> 01:13:28,744
- I'd like to have this
engraved, if I could.

1213
01:13:28,745 --> 01:13:29,578
- [Employee] Of course.

1214
01:13:29,579 --> 01:13:32,670
- And uh, this is for everything.

1215
01:13:33,816 --> 01:13:37,899
(bright, upbeat Christmas music)

1216
01:13:50,620 --> 01:13:53,399
- [Photographer] Okay,
everyone, and smile.

1217
01:13:53,400 --> 01:13:54,490
Great. One more.

1218
01:13:56,449 --> 01:13:58,139
♪ Dashing through the snow ♪

1219
01:13:58,140 --> 01:14:00,340
♪ On a one horse open sleigh ♪

1220
01:14:00,341 --> 01:14:02,451
♪ O'er the fields we go ♪

1221
01:14:02,452 --> 01:14:04,833
♪ Laughing all the way, ha ha ha ♪

1222
01:14:04,834 --> 01:14:06,759
- Donald, I'm fine.

1223
01:14:06,760 --> 01:14:09,519
The reason I'm calling is to
tell you that I'm all right.

1224
01:14:09,520 --> 01:14:11,599
- [Donald] But dad, you're
wanted by the police.

1225
01:14:11,600 --> 01:14:12,939
They said to me-
- I don't care what

1226
01:14:12,940 --> 01:14:14,537
they said to you.

1227
01:14:14,538 --> 01:14:16,519
- [Donald] You ran away from them?

1228
01:14:16,520 --> 01:14:17,819
- Does your mother know?

1229
01:14:17,820 --> 01:14:19,259
- She called here when you didn't

1230
01:14:19,260 --> 01:14:20,539
show up in Puerto Vallarta.

1231
01:14:20,540 --> 01:14:21,490
She's cutting her trip short.

1232
01:14:21,491 --> 01:14:23,719
She'll be docking in
San Diego on the 26th.

1233
01:14:23,720 --> 01:14:24,919
- [Gordon] San Diego?

1234
01:14:24,920 --> 01:14:27,341
- You're putting your mother in danger.

1235
01:14:27,342 --> 01:14:29,123
- [Gordon] Hold it, one second.

1236
01:14:30,150 --> 01:14:32,669
- Dad?
- Is that the 26th?

1237
01:14:32,670 --> 01:14:34,620
- Yeah.
- At what time?

1238
01:14:34,621 --> 01:14:36,329
- I don't know. Morning.

1239
01:14:36,330 --> 01:14:37,959
Look, where are you?

1240
01:14:37,960 --> 01:14:39,276
- [Gordon] I don't wanna tell you.

1241
01:14:39,277 --> 01:14:40,206
- But...

1242
01:14:40,207 --> 01:14:41,781
What do you mean you
don't want to tell me?

1243
01:14:41,782 --> 01:14:42,969
- [Gordon] I've gotta
go. The kids need me.

1244
01:14:42,970 --> 01:14:43,803
- What?

1245
01:14:43,804 --> 01:14:46,119
You're still with them?

1246
01:14:46,120 --> 01:14:49,519
Uh, listen, you're not
suffering from that, uh,

1247
01:14:49,520 --> 01:14:51,459
Patty Hearst syndrome, are you?

1248
01:14:51,460 --> 01:14:54,689
You know, identifying
with your kidnappers?

1249
01:14:54,690 --> 01:14:55,754
- [Gordon] Stop that.

1250
01:14:55,755 --> 01:14:56,588
They're just kids.

1251
01:14:56,589 --> 01:14:58,919
- Come on, dad. You can't believe that.

1252
01:14:58,920 --> 01:15:01,009
This girl is wanted for prostitution.

1253
01:15:01,010 --> 01:15:04,029
She cut up her foster father
the day you were kidnapped.

1254
01:15:04,030 --> 01:15:06,479
And the boy's got a rap
sheet you can't believe.

1255
01:15:06,480 --> 01:15:07,869
- Donald, son...

1256
01:15:07,870 --> 01:15:08,949
- If they're caught, they're going back

1257
01:15:08,950 --> 01:15:10,659
to juvenile hall or worse.

1258
01:15:10,660 --> 01:15:12,079
You can bet on that.
- Donald.

1259
01:15:12,080 --> 01:15:13,379
- And then-
- Do I tell you

1260
01:15:13,380 --> 01:15:14,999
I love you enough?

1261
01:15:15,000 --> 01:15:16,654
- [Donald] What?

1262
01:15:16,655 --> 01:15:17,655
Dad? Dad?

1263
01:15:17,656 --> 01:15:20,585
(phone thuds)

1264
01:15:20,586 --> 01:15:21,586
Dad?

1265
01:15:25,333 --> 01:15:30,333
(sawing)
(air dryer whirring)

1266
01:15:30,694 --> 01:15:31,807
(knocking)

1267
01:15:31,808 --> 01:15:33,143
- What?

1268
01:15:33,144 --> 01:15:37,894
- [Gordon] Crystal, what are
you doin' in the men's room?

1269
01:15:38,911 --> 01:15:40,994
(sawing)

1270
01:15:42,805 --> 01:15:44,966
- Come to the party.

1271
01:15:44,967 --> 01:15:47,050
(sawing)

1272
01:15:48,128 --> 01:15:50,019
- What do you think you're doing?

1273
01:15:50,020 --> 01:15:50,853
- It's okay.

1274
01:15:50,853 --> 01:15:51,830
I asked him.

1275
01:15:51,831 --> 01:15:53,747
I can't go home with a cast on my arm.

1276
01:15:55,544 --> 01:15:56,847
- Here, take this.

1277
01:15:56,848 --> 01:15:58,322
Give me the saw.

1278
01:15:58,323 --> 01:15:59,800
- Cool, snacks.

1279
01:15:59,801 --> 01:16:01,301
- Hold very still.

1280
01:16:03,542 --> 01:16:05,625
(sawing)

1281
01:16:07,306 --> 01:16:09,889
(gentle music)

1282
01:16:11,632 --> 01:16:12,632
- 12412.

1283
01:16:15,400 --> 01:16:16,400
Okay, 12418.

1284
01:16:17,890 --> 01:16:20,437
This is good, you can let me out here.

1285
01:16:22,178 --> 01:16:24,761
(gentle music)

1286
01:16:27,840 --> 01:16:31,439
- Now remember we'll be at the
Quality Court till tomorrow.

1287
01:16:31,440 --> 01:16:35,319
Room 420. Just in case you want
to reach us for any reason.

1288
01:16:35,320 --> 01:16:36,320
- She won't need to.

1289
01:16:37,650 --> 01:16:38,850
We're going to miss you.

1290
01:16:40,062 --> 01:16:42,973
You kept us, ah, well, you
tried to keep us honest.

1291
01:16:44,180 --> 01:16:46,407
We'll send you a pinata from Mexico, okay?

1292
01:16:47,874 --> 01:16:48,874
- Thanks.

1293
01:16:50,860 --> 01:16:51,860
Bye, Cam.

1294
01:16:53,870 --> 01:16:55,298
- Yeah.

1295
01:16:55,299 --> 01:16:56,299
Take it easy.

1296
01:16:58,400 --> 01:16:59,400
- Don't I get a kiss?

1297
01:17:01,494 --> 01:17:02,494
- Yeah.

1298
01:17:04,046 --> 01:17:06,928
(kisses)

1299
01:17:06,929 --> 01:17:09,512
(gentle music)

1300
01:17:13,877 --> 01:17:16,053
- I'm sorry for what we did.

1301
01:17:17,557 --> 01:17:19,830
But I'm sorta not, you know?

1302
01:17:21,969 --> 01:17:24,552
(gentle music)

1303
01:17:49,442 --> 01:17:51,838
- [Boy] She's here!

1304
01:17:51,839 --> 01:17:54,672
(boys chattering)

1305
01:17:58,715 --> 01:18:00,906
- [Celeste] Let me look at you.

1306
01:18:00,907 --> 01:18:03,119
- [Cliff] You outdid
yourself this time, Celeste.

1307
01:18:03,120 --> 01:18:05,663
- Thank you.
- Mom, it was fantastic.

1308
01:18:09,547 --> 01:18:12,347
- And you never told me your
daughter was such a looker.

1309
01:18:14,060 --> 01:18:15,710
- Well, of course she's a looker.

1310
01:18:16,641 --> 01:18:20,043
I mean, after all, she
takes after her mama.

1311
01:18:21,800 --> 01:18:26,365
(kissing)
(laughing)

1312
01:18:26,366 --> 01:18:27,199
You tired?

1313
01:18:27,200 --> 01:18:28,757
- No.
- How about a now?

1314
01:18:28,758 --> 01:18:29,831
- No.

1315
01:18:29,832 --> 01:18:31,332
I gotta get goin'.

1316
01:18:32,790 --> 01:18:34,769
Come on, Jenny, get your sweater, sweetie.

1317
01:18:34,770 --> 01:18:35,809
- What do you mean?

1318
01:18:35,810 --> 01:18:37,479
- I told you, Jenny and I are going

1319
01:18:37,480 --> 01:18:39,614
to her mom's for Christmas Eve.

1320
01:18:39,615 --> 01:18:40,570
Get your coat. Come on, Jenny.

1321
01:18:40,571 --> 01:18:41,849
- No, Jenny, wait a minute.

1322
01:18:41,850 --> 01:18:43,829
You didn't tell me that.

1323
01:18:43,830 --> 01:18:46,048
This is the first time
I've heard about it.

1324
01:18:46,049 --> 01:18:47,959
- What did I tell you
at the base? Remember?

1325
01:18:47,960 --> 01:18:49,489
After the party, I said that we're going

1326
01:18:49,490 --> 01:18:51,899
to come back here and have
dinner with your daughter

1327
01:18:51,900 --> 01:18:53,641
and then I was going to take Jenny,

1328
01:18:53,642 --> 01:18:54,475
I was going to take Jenny

1329
01:18:54,476 --> 01:18:55,769
over to her mother's for Christmas Eve.

1330
01:18:55,770 --> 01:18:56,829
I told you.
- No, no, no.

